      "type": "answer",
      "text": "Looking at your BSOD screenshot, this is a **WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR** - a serious hardware-related error in Windows.\n\n## What This Error Means\n\nWHEA (Windows Hardware Error Architecture) errors indicate **hardware-level problems** that Windows cannot correct. Common causes:\n\n| Category | Potential Issues |\n|----------|------------------|\n| **CPU** | Overheating, degradation, unstable overclock |\n| **RAM** | Failing modules, incompatible timings |\n| **Motherboard** | VRM issues, capacitor failure |\n| **Storage** | Failing NVMe/SATA drive |\n| **PSU** | Inadequate/aging power delivery |\n| **Drivers** | Especially GPU or storage drivers |\n\n## Enterprise Root Cause Analysis Framework\n\nTo properly diagnose this, I need to run diagnostic commands on your system:\n\n**Diagnostic Plan:**\n1. **Event Logs** - `Get-WinEvent -FilterHashtable @{LogName='System'; Level=1,2} -MaxEvents 50`\n2. **Memory Dump Analysis** - Check `C:\\Windows\\Minidump\\` for .dmp files\n3. **SFC/DISM** - System file integrity check\n4. **Disk Health** - SMART data via `Get-PhysicalDisk`\n5. **Thermal Assessment** - CPU temps via OpenHardwareMonitor/WMI\n6. **Driver Verifier** - Identify problematic drivers\n\n---\n\n**Before I proceed with running these diagnostics, I have some questions:**",
      "timestamp": 1783146252243
    },
    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "The user is asking me to investigate a BSOD (Blue Screen of Death) error with stop code \"WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR\". They want me to:\n\n1. Investigate using \"proper enterprise root cause analysis\"\n2. Tell them its \"fixibility score using ifix\" (I think they mean iFixit or some scoring system)\n3. Tell them how reliable it is\n4. Whether they can improve PC temperature\n5. Ensure all components are okay\n6. They don't want to stress test components\n7. They want a \"decent assessment\" using PowerShell and Python tools\n\nHowever, I'm in \"Plan Mode\" and cannot execute any commands. I can only read, analyze, and plan. I should:\n\n1. Research the error code to understand what it means\n2. Suggest diagnostic steps3. Provide a plan for investigation\n\nLet me start by understanding what WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR means and what diagnostic approach to take.\n\nWHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR is a Windows Hardware Error Architecture error. It's typically related to:\n- Hardware failures (CPU, RAM, motherboard, GPU)\n- Overheating\n- Power supply issues\n- BIOS/UEFI settings\n- Driver issues\n\nSince I cannot execute commands, I should ask the user if they want me to proceed with a diagnostic plan, or I can provide information about this error and suggest next steps.\n\nActually, looking at the system reminder again - I'm in READ-ONLY mode. I cannot make any edits or run commands. I should provide a plan or ask clarifying questions.\n\nLet me provide a comprehensive analysis plan for this BSOD error.",
      "timestamp": 1783146282380
